Full Awareness After ten years of apprenticeship, Tenno achieved the rank of Zen teacher. One rainy day, he went to visit the famous master Nan-in. When he walked in, the master greeted him with a question, &ldquo;Did you leave your wooden clogs and umbrella on the porch?&rdquo;
&ldquo;Yes,&rdquo; Tenno replied.
&ldquo;Tell me,&rdquo; the master continued, &ldquo;did you place your umbrella to the left of your shoes, or to the right?&rdquo;
